---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="What SmallGrid is and why it exists." canonicalPath="/about/">
  <section class="card">
    <h1 style="margin:0 0 10px;">About SmallGrid</h1>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0;">
      SmallGrid is a collection of practical guides for building homelabs that are small, quiet, and low power —
      the kind you can run in a normal house without it sounding like an aircraft carrier.
    </p>

    <div class="hr"></div>

    <h2 style="margin:0 0 8px;">What you’ll find here</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:0; padding-left: 18px;">
      <li>Jellyfin setups that prioritise reliability and efficiency</li>
      <li>Mini PC homelabs and simple Proxmox layouts</li>
      <li>Remote access done safely (Tailscale first)</li>
      <li>Backups that restore (not “I think it’s backed up?”)</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="hr"></div>

    <p class="muted" style="margin:0;">
      The site may include ads later to cover basic running costs.
      Everything here is written to be useful even if you ignore every single recommendation.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
